{"id":"c44126a1-9096-494c-a814-14a9d46dd7a1","cefr_level":"B1","text_id":"text_001","text_translated":"NASA is now working to record smaller asteroids (small rocky objects that travel around the sun), which are 140 metres wide or more. There are an estimated 25,000 asteroids of this size. So far, only about 8,000 have been recorded. This leaves 17,000 that have not been found yet. These middle-sized asteroids can be very dangerous if they enter Earth's orbit. For example, a much smaller 19-metre asteroid injured 1,200 people when it exploded over Chelyabinsk, Russia in 2013.","version":26,"created_at":"2025-08-31T18:53:02.587869","updated_at":"2025-08-31T18:54:01.123456"}
